OriginalText.Phrase: Be ati omnes qui timent Do-

Note.EditorialCommentary: Treated as dotted rhythms in the CMM Champion edition and the discussion in NJE 15 (commentary pp. 23-4), the coloration in this motive in Discantus, Altus, Tenor 2, and Bassus can be better read as sesquialtera (3:2). Minor color rarely occurs back-to-back in multiple groups, and would also require a switch of rhythmic coloration level during the passage in the Bassus (mm. 55-6, breve/semibreve - semibreve/minim).

OriginalText.Phrase: Beati omnes qui timent Do minum,
